---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import Skills from '../components/Skills.astro';
import Education from '../components/Education.astro';
import Contact from '../components/Contact.astro';
---

<Layout title="Kanan Abdullayev - Hardware Engineer">
	<Hero 
		name="Kanan Abdullayev - Hardware Engineer"
		title="Hardware & Firmware Engineer"
		bio="Engineering student at CTU in Prague, Faculty of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science, specialized in embedded systems and hardware R&D. Passionate about building circuits, starting new hardware projects, testing circuits and debugging to find solutions for mysterious problems. I want to grow in an environment where I can learn from professionals and solve real-world problems, bringing a strong foundation with Microcontrollers, C programming, and Circuit simulation."
	/>

	<main id="projects">
		<div class="container">
			<h2 class="section-heading"><span class="section-num">01.</span>Projects &amp; Labs <div class="heading-line"></div></h2>

			<div class="project-card featured-project rf-receiver-card">
				<div class="rf-content">
					<h3>Digitally Tuned RF Receiver 📻</h3>
					<p>Built a digitally tuned FM radio receiver from scratch using an ESP32 and a TEA5767 module. Overcame physical hardware challenges, such as I2C communication failures, removal of ESP32 signal noise by using proper decoupling capacitors and stabilization of LM386 audio amp by using Zobel network.</p>
					<div class="tags">
						<span class="tag">ESP32</span>
						<span class="tag">TEA5767</span>
						<span class="tag">HardwareDebugging</span>
						<span class="tag">I2C</span>
						<span class="tag">RF Engineering</span>
						<span class="tag">C Programming</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="rf-media">
					<a href="/project-media/everyday_I_am_suffering.mp4" data-type="video" class="lightbox-trigger rf-hero-link">
						<video playsinline class="rf-hero" poster="/project-media/rf_receiver_everyday_thumbnail_1.png">
							<source src="/project-media/everyday_I_am_suffering.mp4" type="video/mp4">
						</video>
					</a>
					<div class="rf-media-grid">
						<div class="rf-grid-item">
							<a href="/project-media/radio_test_2.mp4" data-type="video" class="lightbox-trigger">
								<video playsinline poster="/project-media/rf_receiver_everyday_thumbnail_2.png">
									<source src="/project-media/radio_test_2.mp4" type="video/mp4">
								</video>
							</a>
						</div>
						<div class="rf-grid-item">
							<img src="/project-media/final_product.jpeg" alt="Final Product" class="lightbox-trigger" />
						</div>
						<div class="rf-grid-item">
							<img src="/project-media/soldering_in_lab.jpeg" alt="Soldering in Lab" class="lightbox-trigger" />
						</div>
						<div class="rf-grid-item">
							<img src="/project-media/soldered_tea_module.jpeg" alt="Soldered TEA Module" class="lightbox-trigger" />
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="project-card featured-project dino-bot-card">
				<div class="dino-content">
					<h3>Arduino Dinosaur Bot 🦖</h3>
					<p>Built a physical bot using an Arduino Uno to physically play the Chrome Dinosaur game, using photoresistor as a sensor to trigger servo actuation. This was 3 years ago :)</p>
					<div class="tags">
						<span class="tag">Arduino</span>
						<span class="tag">Servo Control</span>
						<span class="tag">Sensor Integration</span>
						<span class="tag">Game Automation</span>
					</div>
					<div class="links">
						<a href="https://github.com/MerchantHunted/arduino-dino-bot" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn">View GitHub Repo</a>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="dino-media">
					<a href="/project-media/Dinosaur_Game.mp4" data-type="video" class="lightbox-trigger dino-hero-link">
						<video playsinline class="dino-hero" poster="/project-media/dinasaur_game_thumbnail.png">
							<source src="/project-media/Dinosaur_Game.mp4" type="video/mp4">
						</video>
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="lab-folders">
				<details class="folder" open>
					<summary>📁 Circuit Technology</summary>
					<div class="folder-content">
						<div class="labs-grid">
							<div class="project-card lab-card">
								<h3>Operational Amplifier Circuit Analysis</h3>
								<img src="/project-media/op-amp-schematic.jpg" alt="Op-Amp Schematic" class="lightbox-trigger" />
								<p>Designed and simulated an op amp circuit using NI Multisim. Calculated nominal output voltage and evaluated circuit stability by testing input voltage offsets to identify failure thresholds. Performed Monte Carlo analysis on resistor values within a 3kOhm range to determine output voltage minimums, maximums, and statistical distribution.</p>
								<div class="tags">
									<span class="tag">NI Multisim</span>
									<span class="tag">Operational Amplifiers</span>
									<span class="tag">Monte Carlo Analysis</span>
									<span class="tag">Circuit Stability</span>
								</div>
								<div class="links">
									<a href="/OpAmp_Analysis.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn action-btn">View Report</a>
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="project-card lab-card">
								<h3>Diode Harmonic Shaper</h3>
								<img src="/project-media/diode-harmonic-shaper-image.png" alt="Diode Harmonic Shaper Circuit" style="width: 100%; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 1rem;" class="lightbox-trigger" />
								<video src="/project-media/diode-harmonic-shaper-video.mp4" autoplay muted loop playsinline style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/11; object-fit: cover; object-position: center 35%; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;"></video>
								<p>Implemented linear approximation using potentiometers and diode branches to progressively clip and reshape a triangular waveform into a sinusoidal output for harmonic shaping.</p>
								<div class="tags">
									<span class="tag">Piecewise Approximation</span>
									<span class="tag">Diode Networks</span>
									<span class="tag">Wave Shaping</span>
									<span class="tag">Potentiometer Tuning</span>
								</div>
								<div class="links">
									<div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; margin-top: auto; flex-wrap: wrap;">
										<a href="/project-media/diode-harmonic-shaper-report.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn action-btn">View Report</a>
										<a href="/project-media/diode-harmonic-shaper.ms14" download class="btn action-btn">Download Multisim File</a>
									</div>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="folder">
					<summary>📁 Microcontrollers</summary>
					<div class="folder-content">
						<div class="labs-grid">
							<div class="project-card lab-card">
								<h3>Microcontroller I/O Interfacing and Debugging</h3>
								<img src="/project-media/easypic-board.jpg" alt="EasyPIC v7 Board" style="width: 100%; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 1rem;" class="lightbox-trigger" />
								<p>Programmed an EasyPIC v7 development board to manage I/O operations, specifically controlling LED arrays and interpreting button states. Configured hardware registers (ANSEL, TRIS, and LAT) to define port functionality on PORTB and PORTC. Developed control logic to trigger specific even/odd LED patterns based on corresponding hardware button inputs.</p>
								<div class="tags">
									<span class="tag">EasyPIC v7</span>
									<span class="tag">Hardware Debugging</span>
									<span class="tag">Microcontrollers</span>
									<span class="tag">I/O Operations</span>
								</div>
								<div class="links">
									<a href="/MicroC_IO_interface.c" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn">View C Code</a>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="folder">
					<summary>📁 Materials for Power Electrical Engineering</summary>
					<div class="folder-content">
						<div class="labs-grid">
							<div class="project-card lab-card">
								<h3>Investigation of Magnetic Losses</h3>
								<div style="display: flex; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 1rem; width: 100%;">
									<img src="/project-media/magnetic-oscilloscope.jpg" style="width: 50%; height: auto; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 8px; aspect-ratio: 4/3;" class="lightbox-trigger" />
									<img src="/project-media/magnetic-setup.jpg" style="width: 50%; height: auto; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 8px; aspect-ratio: 4/3;" class="lightbox-trigger" />
								</div>
								<p>Investigated magnetic (watt) losses in soft magnetic materials by measuring hysteresis loops. Set up and operated physical measurement circuits including a variable transformer, multimeters, and a current converter. Utilized an oscilloscope to capture the primary magnetization curve and calculate specific energy dissipation.</p>
								<div class="tags">
									<span class="tag">Oscilloscopes</span>
									<span class="tag">Hardware Measurement</span>
									<span class="tag">Electromagnetics</span>
									<span class="tag">Data Analysis</span>
								</div>
								<div class="links">
									<a href="/Investigation_of_Magnetic_Losses.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn action-btn">View Report</a>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</div>
	</main>

